complete_model_interaction.output:
Step-by-step reasoning:
• The key psychological mechanism is fairness: proposers adjust their offers based on the relative merit in token contributions. When the opponent’s tokens exceed the participant’s tokens, the fairness norm may call for a higher proposed percentage to the opponent and vice versa.
• This mechanism is captured by computing a normalized fairness index based on token differences.
• We use a logistic function to map the linear combination of the fairness index and a baseline preference to a percentage in the range [0, 100].
• Only two learnable parameters are introduced: one that captures the baseline tendency (theta0) and one that captures the sensitivity to relative token imbalance (theta1). Their numerical bounds are set generously.
• The observable proposal percentage (proposed_perc) is thus modeled as a transformation of the fairness index, computed from the tokens gathered by each agent.
• The dataset variables used in the model are token_opp and token_self, and the model directly predicts proposed_perc.

<MODEL>
proposed_perc = 100/(1+exp(-(theta0 + theta1*((token_opp-token_self)/(token_self+token_opp))))
</MODEL>

